name: Biko
author: Catherine S
ingredients: 3 tablespoons coconut preserves (such as Phil Supreme®)
directions: Soak rice overnight in the water
Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Cook the soaked rice over medium heat in a saucepan with the soaking water, 1/2 can of coconut milk, and white sugar, stirring constantly, until tender and thickened, about 20 minutes
Pour into the prepared baking pan
Stir together the brown sugar, remaining 1/2 can of coconut milk, and coconut preserves in a small saucepan, and bring to a boil
Pour the mixture carefully over the rice
Bake in the preheated oven until the topping thickens, about 25 minutes
Cool completely; cut into squares to serve
